## User Login [/api/v1/auth/login]
### Login a user [POST]

A user can login using this action. It takes a JSON
object containing a username, and password

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "username": "david",
            "password": "1234",
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Location: /api/v1/auth/login

    + Body

            {
                "auth_token": "eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJpYXQiOjE1MzMzODc0OTUsIm5iZiI6MTUzMzM4NzQ5NSwianRpIjoiZTI3MWEzMDQtYWYyNS00MjBhLWExZTEtZWRjNThjMTA4NzI5IiwiZXhwIjoxNTMzMzg4Mzk1LCJpZGVudGl0eSI6MywiZnJlc2giOmZhbHNlLCJ0eXBlIjoiYWNjZXNzIn0.rEGC_7j_ERDrX5zHluTSaGGFOj5bg6ypRVMIQ9XloJk",
                "message": "Logged in Successfully"
            }

## Creating an entry and Listing all entries [/api/v1/entries]

### List All entries [GET]

A logged in user can get all his/her entries using this action

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Location: /api/v1/entries
            Authorization: Bearer auth_token
    
    + Body

            {
                "status": "success",
                "entries": [
                    {
                        "entry_id": 1,
                        "user_id": 1,
                        "title": "Another entry",
                        "description": "This another entry",
                        "creation_time": "2018-08-04 14:27:00"
                    },
                    {
                        "entry_id": 2,
                        "user_id": 1,
                        "title": "Entry 2",
                        "description": "This is entry 2",
                        "creation_time": "2018-08-04 14:27:24"
                    }
                ]
            }

### Post an entry [POST]

A logged in user can add an entry to his/her diary using this action

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "title": "Entry 2",
            "description": "This is entry 2"
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Location: /api/v1/entries
            Authorization: Bearer auth_token
    
    + Body

            {
                "message": "Entry has been created",
                "Created entry": [
                    {
                        "entry_id": 1,
                        "user_id": 1,
                        "title": "Another entry",
                        "description": "This another entry",
                        "creation_time": "2018-08-04 14:27:00"
                    }
                ]
            }

## Getting, updating, and deleting a single entry [/api/v1/entries/1]

### Getting a single entry [GET]

A logged in user can get a single entry using this action

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Location: /api/v1/entries/1
            Authorization: Bearer auth_token
    
    + Body

            {
                "status": "success",
                "entries": [
                    {
                        "entry_id": 1,
                        "user_id": 1,
                        "title": "Another entry",
                        "description": "This another entry",
                        "creation_time": "2018-08-04 14:27:00"
                    }
                ]
            }

### Updating an entry [PUT]

A logged in user can update an entry in his/her diary using this action

+ Request

        {
            "title": "Update10",
            "description": "This is the 10th update"
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Location: /api/v1/entries/1
            Authorization: Bearer auth_token
    
    + Body

            {
                "message": "Entry has been updated successfully",
                "Original entry": [
                    {
                        "entry_id": 1,
                        "user_id": 1,
                        "title": "Another entry",
                        "description": "This another entry",
                        "creation_time": "2018-08-04 14:27:00"
                    }
                ],
                "Updated entry": [
                    {
                        "entry_id": 1,
                        "user_id": 1,
                        "title": "Update10",
                        "description": "This is the 10th update",
                        "creation_time": "2018-08-04 14:27:00"
                    }
                ]
            }

### Deleting an entry [DELETE]

A logged in user can delete a single entry using this action

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Location: /api/v1/entries/1
            Authorization: Bearer auth_token
    
    + Body

            {
                "meassge": "The entry has been deleted",
                "Deleted entry": [
                    {
                        "entry_id": 1,
                        "user_id": 1,
                        "title": "Update12",
                        "description": "This is the 12th update",
                        "creation_time": "2018-08-04 14:27:00"
                    }
                ]
            }